text: Ali Khadivar (; born 11 November 1989) is an Iranian sprinter. He won an individual bronze medal at the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games in the 400 m, and holds a national record in this event. ==References== Category:Iranian male sprinters Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games competitors for Iran
